    "initialsConvention": "Old Mysuru (southern Karnataka) convention: one or two initials precede the given name — first initial = native village/town, second = father's given name; e.g. H. D. Deve Gowda (Haradanahalli + Doddegowda), B. S. Yediyurappa (Bookanakere + Siddalingappa), S. M. Krishna (Somanahalli + Mallaiah), D. K. Shivakumar (Doddaalahalli + Kempegowda), K. R. Ramesh. Single father-initial forms (M. Manjunath, B. Savitha) are extremely common on voter rolls, FIRs and school records; the initials are usually never expanded except in official documents, and the same person may appear with and without initials in different databases. In north Karnataka (Kittur/Kalyana Karnataka) surnames (Patil, Kulkarni, Biradar, Hiremath) largely replace initials; a village-name surname (e.g. Jamakhandi, Gokak) also occurs. Coastal Karnataka uses community surnames (Shetty, Rai, Poojary, D'Souza) with Western-style ordering.",
